# Taskflow - Cursor Project Rules
# Stack: Python 3.12 - Django 5.x - DRF - PostgreSQL - pytest - ruff - mypy
#
# Detailed rules live in .cursor/rules/. This file is the always-on summary.
# Read .cursor/rules/00-project-context.mdc for the full picture.

## Golden Rules
- Be Pythonic, be Djangonic. Use the ORM; let the database do the work.
- The Model IS the service layer. No Service classes for CRUD.
- Validate at the serializer edge. Bad input returns a clean 400, never a DB 500.
- Everything is typed (mypy) and linted (ruff) before it merges.
- Every endpoint and every bug fix ships with a test.

## Logging
- Default to logger.debug(). Reserve logger.info() for key production events.
- Always logger.exception() inside except blocks (never logger.error()).
- Never use print() in application code.

## Django ORM
- Domain models extend common.models.BaseModel (UUID pk + created/modified + indexes).
- Inherit BaseModel.Meta; extend (never replace) BaseModel.Meta.indexes.
- One model per file under models/, re-exported from models/__init__.py.
- select_related for forward FK, prefetch_related for reverse FK / M2M.
- annotate() for aggregates; bulk_create() for batch writes; never .save() in a loop.
- IntegerChoices for ordered enums (priority); TextChoices for status.

## DRF
- PrimaryKeyRelatedField(queryset=Model.objects.all()) - never .none().
- ChoiceFilter for IntegerChoices/TextChoices fields - never CharFilter(icontains) on numbers.
- Separate list vs detail serializers; switch via get_serializer_class().
- Paginate every list endpoint (page size 20).

## Security
- Read all secrets from environment variables. Never hardcode or commit them.
- Error messages must be consumer-friendly. Never leak model names, ORM, SQL, or paths.

## Git
- Feature branch per issue; PR into main; never commit directly to main.
- Conventional Commits. No em dash in commit/branch/PR text.

## Never Generate
- print() in application code.
- .save() inside loops.
- CharFilter(lookup_expr="icontains") on a numeric field.
- PrimaryKeyRelatedField(queryset=Model.objects.none()).
- bare except: or logger.error() inside an except block.
- comments that merely narrate what the code does.
